Robert M. Parker, Jr., sings the praises of Perrier-Jouet Grand Brut:

“Delightfully fresh, creamy, fruity and frothy”

errier-Jouet Grand Brut 150th Anniversary Cuvee demonstrates that non-vintage

Champagne can often be better than vintage Champagne. Perrier-Jouet Grand

Brut is rich and well-balanced, flavorsome and bone dry, revealing in full measure the elements that constitute a great Champagne.

Perrier-Jouet is a relatively small Champagne firm that specializes in superior non-vintage and a remarkable grande marque Champagne—Fleur de Champagne.

The 150th Anniversary Cuvee celebrates 150 years of Champagne shipments from Perrier- Jouet to the United States. The excellence of this wine reflects the importance of the occasion. It is also of historic interest to note that in the 19th century Perrier-Jouet were purveyors of Champagne to Leopold I of the Belgians, Emperor Napoleon III and Queen Victoria.
